text: Antonio de Celano (died 1455) was a Roman Catholic prelate who served as Bishop of Lettere-Gragnano (1440–1455). ==Biography== On 26 September 1440, Antonio de Celano was appointed during the papacy of Pope Eugene IV as Bishop of Lettere-Gragnano. He served as Bishop of Lettere-Gragnano until his death in 1455. == References == ==External links and additional sources== * (for Chronology of Bishops) * (for Chronology of Bishops) Category:15th-century Roman Catholic bishops Category:Bishops appointed by Pope Eugene IV Category:1455 deaths
